good at dealing with other people's

...So, why is a tiny girl like Serena
doing adventurer stuff? And all by
herself, too.\n< Erika >

You gotta tell me that before I let you
go home.\n< Erika >

What I do and for what purpose is none
of Erika- sama's concern.\n< Serena >
You should just leave me be.\n< Serena >

Come on, don't say that. We've shared a
bath together, right?\n< Erika >
\n< Serena >...

Talking things out is important.
Seriously. There's only so much a person
can do alone.\n< Erika >
\n< Serena >...

\n< Serena >...Actually, I'm searching for a unicorn
for a certain reason.
\n< Erika >A unicorn? That horse with a horn?

Yes. Well, it's more like a donkey in
size... just the right size for me to
ride.\n< Serena >
Its name is Splendor.\n< Serena >

Oh... huh? Searching for something
means... it's lost?\n< Erika >

So you mean... you originally owned the
unicorn?\n< Erika >

Eh? The legendary? Mythical creature?
What level of rich are you? Some kind of
noble or royalty?\n< Erika >

...That unicorn was kidnapped by
someone. It's a precious creature, so I
must retrieve it.\n< Serena >

It has a horn that cures all diseases,
right? Yeah, well, it makes sense it
would be targeted.\n< Erika >

But hey, about getting it back... do you
have any leads? Any idea who the culprit
might be?\n< Erika >

The kidnapper took the unicorn away in
broad daylight on a cart.\n< Serena >

According to witnesses, it was a
conspicuous red- decorated carriage.\n< Serena >

It was done so openly that everyone
present thought it was a regular
transport.\n< Serena >

There was also talk of changing the
grazing land at the time.\n< Serena >

I realized what had happened half a day
later. I left home and chased after that
carriage.\n< Serena >

Following the remaining wheel tracks and
various rumors, as well as some other
slight traces... I was able to track it
down to near this area.\n< Serena >

Therefore, the kidnapper must have fled
to the town just east of here... what
was it called? Something-something town.\n< Serena >

Ahh, I see. It's been brought into a
troublesome place.\n< Erika >

Yeah, if you're gonna deal with shady
stuff around here, that's the place to
go.\n< Erika >

Whether they plan to take it abroad or
break it down for parts to sell, they
won't have trouble finding a buyer.\n< Erika >

I won't let that happen. I'll rescue it
before then.\n< Serena >

And so, I've been traveling day and
night to get here, but... who would have
thought the only bridge in the area
would be closed.\n< Serena >
\n< Erika >So that's why you became an adventurer.

Yes. I heard that if I complete quests
and build up a track record, the guild
will issue me a pass to cross the
bridge.\n< Serena >

I was hesitant, but I decided it would
be faster than taking a detour to the
next bridge.\n< Serena >

I see. I think I understand the
situation now.\n< Erika >

But hey, if it wasn't urgent, you'd be
stuck here anyway, right?\n< Erika >

Then why not just call some servants or
something and leave the rest to them?\n< Erika >

After all, adventurers are usually on
the hiring side, right? There's no need
for Serena herself to go on an
adventure.\n< Erika >

\n< Erika >More importantly, do your parents even
know about this?

I left without telling my parents. If I
had told them... they certainly wouldn't
have allowed it.\n< Serena >

You're absolutely right, Erika-sama. I
myself think that's what I should do.
Anyone would say I'm doing something
foolish.\n< Serena >

But... that child, Splendor is my
irreplaceable... my only friend.\n< Serena >

If I don't feed her by hand, she won't
eat a single carrot. If I don't stroke
her to sleep, she'll cry all night long.\n< Serena >

When I play the piano, she jumps around
next to me. When I was scolded and
crying, she was there beside me.\n< Serena >
That child, that child...\n< Serena >

The thought of her being in some unknown
place suffering terrible, horrible
things while I'm here...\n< Serena >
\n< Erika >...

I'm sure even at this moment, she is
calling out for me.\n< Serena >

And I want to be the one to answer that
call myself.\n< Serena >
No... I should be the one.\n< Serena >
That's why I'm here.\n< Serena >

No matter how foolish or irrational this
decision is. No matter how wrong it is.
I will stand by my choice.\n< Serena >

...Even if you face terrible
consequences?\n< Erika >
I am prepared for that.\n< Serena >
"Prepared," huh... Ah, damn it.\n< Erika >
?\n< Serena >
...Alright. I'll help you.\n< Erika >

What? Where in our conversation did you
find a reason to assist me?\n< Serena >

This is a matter for me and my family. I
have no intention of involving others.\n< Serena >

Once I've heard it all, there's no way I
can just ignore it...\n< Erika >

Besides, I have my own things to take
care of, and I'm not saying we should
stick together as a party or anything.\n< Erika >

But if you're in danger, I can at least
help out with that.\n< Erika >
I said your help is unnecessary...\n< Serena >
\n< Erika >The top priority is!

To rescue that unicorn-chan, right? Am I
wrong?\n< Erika >
\n< Serena >Mmm...

Then you should gladly accept my help.
You were in quite a bind, weren't you?\n< Erika >
...I won't deny it.\n< Serena >

Otherwise, you could have just kept
denying it when I pressed you for
answers.\n< Erika >

Just so you know, keeping it a secret
was the right move.\n< Erika >

If word got out that a unicorn was
involved, all sorts of bad characters
would come swarming in.\n< Erika >

In that regard, this Erika-chan is one
of the good guys! Man, Serena, you're
lucky!\n< Erika >

To have such a fun, nice, powerful, and
incidentally beautiful helper... all
because you let her take a bath and play
with her hair!\n< Erika >

Oops, hehehe! As for the reward, how
about a nice sum of gold once we find
unicorn-chan?\n< Erika >
\n< Serena >...Haa...

Honestly, you are so self-centered and
pushy...\n< Serena >

\n< Serena >And yet, you're also considerate and
sincere.

From the very first time you spoke to me
until now, I can tell you've always been
concerned about me.\n< Serena >

I was so lost and felt so alone... If
you're offering to help, I couldn't be
more grateful.\n< Serena >

But let me be clear. This is my problem.
I have no intention of involving you
more than necessary.\n< Serena >

Only help me when I ask for it. It may
sound selfish, but I will pay you for
your trouble.\n< Serena >

Hehe! Alright! That settles it then!
Let's have a toast to celebrate!!\n< Erika >
\n< Erika >Come on, grab your mug!

\n< Serena >Just so you know, I'll only join you for
a moderate amount.

Oh, Miss, what brings you to a place
like this? You had some work to do,
didn't you?\n< Waitress >

Did the master take care of the guild's
request for you?\n< Waitress >

Oh, a young lady in such a place? You
had some work to do, didn't you?\n< Waitress >

The guild's request, did the master ask
for it?\n< Waitress >

"You don't have to deal with the
customers properly. If you don't brush
them off appropriately, they'll get
increasingly presumptuous."\n< Waitress >

"Geez, the regulars keep clamoring for
Serena-chan to come out."\n< Waitress >

"Maybe I should serve them in a
miniskirt with bare legs, huh?"\n< Waitress >
It's okay, it's okay.\n< Waitress >

As long as you live a life without
shame, I'm sure God will protect you in
the end.\n< Waitress >
There are various small dishes laid out.\n< Serena >

It seems that it's good to eat this kind
of thing when drinking alcohol. I have
no idea what makes it good though.\n< Serena >
I'm still working.\n< Serena >
